    {
        "content": "<p>Once again one of the problems here is the types of things not being what you think they are, you should get into the habit of using the widgets like in this gif Patrick made<br>\n<span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110031\">Patrick Massot</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/Christopher.20Hoskin/near/220710143\">said</a>:</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/yk7K9Hzs2prreMTFrhIQ2PRI/nat_vs_int.gif\">nat_vs_int.gif</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/yk7K9Hzs2prreMTFrhIQ2PRI/nat_vs_int.gif\" title=\"nat_vs_int.gif\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/yk7K9Hzs2prreMTFrhIQ2PRI/nat_vs_int.gif\"></a></div><p>to check the types are what you expect.</p>\n<p>In your first lemma, <code>1/2</code> is the natural number floor division <code>1/2</code> which is in fact 0. So the lemma isn't true</p>",
        "id": 221614824,
        "sender_full_name": "Alex J. Best",
        "timestamp": 1609825181
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The version first lemma you really want is in mathlib as <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/real.sqrt_eq_rpow\">docs#real.sqrt_eq_rpow</a> btw</p>",
